author: @avikamath9676
text: Great  video. To answer that dude's question, we rely on t-distributions and not on z-tables because in most practical cases the sigma is unknown. If we do know sigma, and the sample size is greater than 30, then by invoking central limit theorem, we can go with z-tables.
